  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents two diagrams of particles of gas in an apparatus with two chambers that are connected by a valve. In the first diagram, the gas particles are shown close together in the left chamber of the apparatus, which is labeled P sub i. The valve is closed and no particles are shown in the right chamber, which is labeled 0 atmospheres. In the second diagram, the valve between the chambers has been opened and the gas particles are equally distributed across both chambers. The chambers are labeled P sub f equals P sub i divided by 2.\" height=\"264\" src=\"/images/4d3dee63cd02aecacdcf2d0573f4c6c9.png\" width=\"220\"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A sample of an ideal gas at <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P sub i\"><math alttext=\"P sub i\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>P</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is initially confined to one chamber of the apparatus represented above, and the other chamber is initially evacuated. The valve connecting the chambers is opened, and the gas expands at constant temperature to fill both chambers. Which of the following best describes <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"delta S\"><math alttext=\"delta S\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi><mi>S</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> for the process?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i4",
    "choices": [
      {
